modules.description: Splits multi-line strings into lists of lines and removes leading whitespace uniformly across all lines. Processes strings to align their indentation, making them easier to read in source code. Useful for formatting multi-line error messages, SQL queries, or configuration strings directly written in OCaml code.

The module contains two empty child modules with no defined functionality, data types, or operations. Since neither child module provides any elements, there are no values, functions, or types available for use. As a result, no meaningful operations or examples can be demonstrated.
